The paper deals with the enumeration complexity of Unions of Conjunctive Queries (UCQs), which is a topic in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LO. The use of complexity assumptions and the study of tractability make cs.AI a possible sub-category as well. The paper also involves the study of algorithms and data structures, which could place it in cs.DS. Finally, the paper involves the study of computational complexity, which could make cs.CC a relevant sub-category.
